pes_dql — Pandemic Experiment Scenario (Q-Learning v2)

Variant of the pes experiment with an enhanced Q-Learning algorithm featuring
three improvements over the baseline: Double Q-Learning, exponential ε-decay
with warm-up, and Potential-Based Reward Shaping (PBRS).  A Bayesian
optimisation pipeline (Optuna / TPE) searches over 8 hyperparameters.

## Key Features — Q-Learning v2:
- **Double Q-Learning**: eliminates maximisation bias (two independent Q-tables)
- **Exponential ε-decay with warm-up**: better exploration schedule
- **PBRS (Ng et al., 1999)**: reward shaping that preserves optimal policy
- Bayesian optimisation over 8 hyperparameters (Optuna, TPE sampler)
- Resumable optimisation via SQLite persistence (--resume YYYY-MM-DD)
- Best Q-table preserved in memory during search (no lossy re-training)
- Infeasible-action masking in evaluation (consistent with __main__.py)
- Console-based output with ANSI colour formatting

## RL-Agent Technical Specification:
- **State space**: (resources_left, city_number, severity)
  - Resources: 0-30 values
  - City/Trial number: 0-10 values
  - Severity: 0-9 values
- **Action space**: Resource allocation (0-10, discrete)
- **Training**: up to 1,200,000 episodes using Double Q-Learning
- **Q-Table dimensions**: 31 × 11 × 10 × 11
- **Policy**: Greedy (deterministic) with exponential ε-decay during training
- **Confidence estimation**: Entropy-based metacognitive scores
- **Training seed**: CONFIG.SEED (default 42) — reproducible across runs

## Bayesian Optimisation — Search Space:
| Parameter        | Range                 | Scale       | Origin |
|------------------|-----------------------|-------------|--------|
| learning_rate    | [0.05, 0.30]          | logarithmic | Base   |
| discount_factor  | [0.90, 0.999]         | linear      | Base   |
| epsilon_initial  | [0.50, 1.00]          | linear      | Base   |
| epsilon_min      | [0.01, 0.10]          | logarithmic | Base   |
| num_episodes     | [150 000, 500 000]    | step 10 000 | Base   |
| warmup_ratio     | [0.02, 0.15]          | linear      | New    |
| target_ratio     | [0.40, 0.80]          | linear      | New    |
| penalty_coeff    | [1e-4, 0.30]          | logarithmic | New    |

## Experiment Structure:
- Total Experiment: 1
- Blocks: 8
- Sequences per Block: 8 (64 total sequences)
- Trials per Sequence: 3-10 (approximately 360 total trials)
- Decision per Trial: Resource allocation to a single city

## Core Modules:
- **pes_dql/__main__.py**: Experiment execution loop (RL-Agent)
- **pes_dql/ext/optimize_rl.py**: Bayesian optimisation pipeline (8 params)
- **pes_dql/ext/train_rl.py**: Standalone RL-Agent training (Double Q + PBRS)
- **pes_dql/ext/pandemic.py**: Gym environment and enhanced QLearning()
- **pes_dql/src/exp_utils.py**: Severity calculations and aggregation
- **pes_dql/src/log_utils.py**: Dual-stream logging (console + file)
- **pes_dql/src/pygameMediator.py**: RL-Agent response generation with entropy-based confidence
- **pes_dql/src/result_formatter.py**: Report generation and visualisation
- **pes_dql/src/terminal_utils.py**: ANSI colour formatting utilities
- **pes_dql/config/CONFIG.py**: Experiment configuration (incl. SEED)

## Files Generated (optimisation, inputs/<date>_BAYESIAN_OPT/):
- q_best_<date>.npy: Best Q-Table from optimisation
- rewards_best_<date>.npy: Reward history of the best training run
- best_params_<date>.json: Best hyperparameters + per-trial seed + mean_perf
- repro_fingerprint_<date>.json: Environment fingerprint (numpy/python/CSV-hashes/git/SEED)
- optimization_results_<date>.txt: Full report (all trials, best params)
- optimization_history_<date>.png: Convergence plot (completed trials only)
- hyperparameter_importances_<date>.png: Parameter importance (fANOVA)
- optuna_study_<date>.db: SQLite database (resumable via --resume YYYY-MM-DD)
- _best_artifacts.npz / _best_artifacts.json: Pickle-free best Q-table cache

## Files Generated (training, inputs/<date>_RL_TRAIN/):
- q_<date>.npy, rewards_<date>.npy, confsrl_<date>.npy
- training_config_<date>.txt
- random_player_{sequence,normalised}_performance_<date>.png
- rl_agent_{rewards_vs_episodes,sequence_performance,normalised_performance,cumulative_performance,confidences,remapped_confidences}_<date>.png

## Files Generated (experiment, outputs/<date>_RL_AGENT/):
- PES_DQL_<session_id>.txt: Experiment configuration snapshot
- PES_DQL_responses_<session_id>.txt: Trial-by-trial responses (severity, allocation, confidence, timing)
- PES_DQL_movement_log_<session_id>.npy: Movement data
- PES_DQL_results_<session_id>.json: Performance summary (per-block stats, percentiles, improvement)
- PES_DQL_results_<session_id>.png: Performance plots
- PES_DQL_log_<session_id>.txt: Console log (dual-stream, written next to outputs/)

## Usage:
- Execute experiment:       python3 -m pes_dql
- Train new RL-Agent:       python3 -m pes_dql.ext.train_rl
- Run Bayesian optimisation: python3 -m pes_dql.ext.optimize_rl [n_trials] [--resume YYYY-MM-DD]

## Documentation:
- **mejoras_qlearning.md**: Theory and implementation of the 3 QL improvements
- **sugerencias.md**: Future improvement roadmap and Transformer analysis

## Configuration:
Flexible configuration via config/CONFIG.py with parameters for:
- Player type selection (RL-Agent)
- Resource availability and severity bounds
- Block/sequence/trial structure (8×8×3-10)
- Reproducibility (SEED = 42 for Q-Learning training)
- Output preferences and verbosity levels

